  <h2>Bigha se Acre nikalne ka Formula</h2>
  <p><strong>Acre = Bigha &times; 0.625</strong> (Pucca Bigha, UP/Bihar). Ye isliye, kyunki 1 Acre = 43,560 sq ft hota hai aur 1 Pucca Bigha = 27,225 sq ft — to 27,225 &divide; 43,560 = 0.625.</p>
  <h2>Bigha to Acre state-wise kyu badalta hai</h2>
  <p>Acre poore India me standard hai (43,560 sq ft), lekin <strong>Bigha har state me alag</strong> hota hai. UP/Bihar ka Pucca Bigha 27,225 sq ft ka hai to 1 Acre = 1.6 Bigha banta hai. West Bengal ka Bigha 14,400 sq ft ka hai, isliye wahan 1 Acre = lagbhag 3.02 Bigha hota hai. Rajasthan aur MP me bhi alag values milti hain.</p>
  <p>Isliye Bigha to Acre nikalne se pehle apna state/Bigha type upar calculator me zaroor chunein. State-wise saare units ke liye <a href="https://zameennaplo.in/">main converter</a> use karein.</p>

